headline.main: A New York Times/CBS News Poll on the Democratic Race

docs.lead_paragraph: Although her lead over Bernie Sanders has slipped since September, Hillary Rodham Clinton is dominating the race for the Democratic nomination, buoyed by primary voters’ perceptions of her experience and leadership. Mr. Sanders, who trails by double digits, is preferred by those who want change, and he holds distinct advantages on speaking the truth and not being beholden to special interests, according to the latest New York Times/CBS News poll.
